Questions:
What is the primary goal of the research study titled "Expanding Rural Health Cancer Control Capacity: Focus on Cancer Survivorship"?

A) To evaluate the effectiveness of new cancer treatment medications for rural patients;
B) To assess the impact of a telehealth survivorship care plan combined with patient navigator assistance on rural cancer survivors;
C) To compare the outcomes of urban versus rural cancer survivors without any intervention;
D) To provide financial assistance to rural cancer survivors for their medical expenses.

Correct answer: B

Which aspect of the study is considered experimental for the participants?
A) Completing a baseline survey about their cancer experience;
B) Receiving standard cancer treatment and follow-up care;
C) Participating in a telehealth visit with a nurse practitioner and a research nurse to receive a personalized survivorship care plan;
D) Being provided with a $25 gift card for completing an interview or focus group at the end of the study.

Correct answer: C

How will the study team protect your confidential information?
A) By publishing all participant data online for transparency;
B) By storing data in a public database without password protection;
C) By limiting access to Personal Health Information (PHI) and de-identifying research data stored in a secure, password-protected database;
D) By sharing participant information with all study sponsors without restrictions.

Correct answer: C) By limiting access to Personal Health Information (PHI) and de-identifying research data stored in a secure, password-protected database.
